      "⟨f x, ?_, ?_⟩`, where we have to prove that `f x ∈ B` and `f x ≠ b`.\n\nGiven that `hx1 : x ∈ A`, since `image f A = B`, `f x ∈ B`.\n\nIf `f x = b`, then since `f a = b` and `f` is injective on `A`, we get `x = a`, contradicting `hx2 : x ≠ a`.\n\nFor injectivity, suppose that `F ⟨x1, hx1, hx1'⟩ = F ⟨x2, hx2, hx2'⟩`, that is, `f x1 = f x2` with both in `A`, then by `h1`, `x1 = x2`.\n\nFor surjectivity, suppose `y ∈ B` and `y ≠ b`, then since `image f A = B`, there exists `x ∈ A` such that `f x = y`. Moreover, since `f x = y ≠ b = f a`, we must have `x ≠ a` (by `h1`). So `y = f x` and `x ∈ A`, `x ≠ a`. Hence `x ∈ A \\ {a}`, and `F ⟨x, _⟩ = y`.\n\nThus, we can make a bijective function between `A \\ {a}` and `B \\ {b}` using `f`, and then use `Equiv.ofBijective`.\n\nBut perhaps we can do better with `Function.Embedding` and `Function.Surjection`, but here, `Equiv.ofBijective` is better since we need `↑(A \\ {a}) ≃ ↑(B \\ {b})`.\n\nSo perhaps we should do the following:\n\n1. Define `F : {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} → {y : V | y ∈ B ∧ y ≠ b}` as `x ↦ ⟨f x.val, _⟩`.\n2. Prove that it is injective.\n3. Prove that it is surjective.\n4. Define an equivalence from it using `Equiv.ofBijective`.\n\nAlternatively, use `Set.image` and then show the image is `B \\ {b}`.\n\nBut perhaps `Equiv.ofBijective` is better because it directly constructs the equivalence from the bijective function.\n\nIn Lean, the equivalence is between the two coerced sets as types. The coercion `↑(A \\ {a})` is `{x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a}`.\n\n#### Lean Proof\n\n1. Define `F : {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} → {y : V | y ∈ B ∧ y ≠ b}` as follows:\n   - For `x : {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a}`, `F x = ⟨f x.val, ...⟩`.\n   - Here, we have to prove that",
      "by\n  have h5 : ↑(A \\ {a}) = {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} := by\n    ext x\n    simp [Set.mem_diff]\n    <;>\n    (try aesop) <;>\n    (try simp_all [Set.mem_singleton_iff]) <;>\n    (try tauto)\n  \n  have h6 : ↑(B \\ {b}) = {x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} := by\n    ext x\n    simp [Set.mem_diff]\n    <;>\n    (try aesop) <;>\n    (try simp_all [Set.mem_singleton_iff]) <;>\n    (try tauto)\n  \n  have h7 : ({x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} : Set U) ∼ ({x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} : Set V) := by\n    have h7₁ : ({x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} : Set U) ∼ ({x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} : Set V) := by\n      -- Define a function from A \\ {a} to B \\ {b}\n      have h7₂ : ∀ (x : U), x ∈ {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} → f x ∈ {x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} := by\n        intro x hx\n        have h7₃ : x ∈ A := hx.1\n        have h7₄ : x ≠ a := hx.2\n        have h7₅ : f x ∈ B := by\n          have h7₆ : f x ∈ image f A := by\n            apply Set.mem_image_of_mem\n            exact h7₃\n          rw [h2] at *\n          exact h7₆\n        have h7₆ : f x ≠ b := by\n          intro h7₇\n          have h7₈ : f x = b := h7₇\n          have h7₉ : f x = f a := by\n            rw [h4] at *\n            exact h7₈\n          have h7₁₀ : x = a := by\n            have h7₁₁ : x ∈ A := h7₃\n            have h7₁₂ : a ∈ A := h3\n            have h7₁₃ : one_one_on f A := h1\n            have h7₁₄ : x ∈ A := h7₃\n            have h7₁₅ : a ∈ A := h3\n            have h7₁₆ : f x = f a := h7₉\n            exact h7₁₃ h7₁₄ h7₁₅ h7₁₆\n          contradiction\n        exact ⟨h7₅, h7₆⟩\n      -- Define the inverse function\n      have h7₃ : ∀ (y : V), y ∈ {x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} → ∃ (x : U), x ∈ {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} ∧ f x = y := by\n        intro y hy\n        have h7₄ : y ∈ B := hy.1\n        have h7₅ : y ≠ b := hy.2\n        have h7₆ : y ∈ image f A := by\n          rw [h2] at *\n          exact h7₄\n        obtain ⟨x, hx₁, hx₂⟩ := h7₆\n        have h7₇ : x ∈ A := hx₁\n        have h7₈ : f x = y := hx₂\n        have h7₉ : x ≠ a := by\n          intro h7₁₀\n          have h7₁₁ : x = a := h7₁₀\n          have h7₁₂ : f x = f a := by rw [h7₁₁]\n          have h7₁₃ : f x = y := h7₈\n          have h7₁₄ : f a = b := h4\n          have h7₁₅ : y = b := by\n            calc\n              y = f x := by rw [h7₁₃]\n              _ = f a := by rw [h7₁₂]\n              _ = b := by rw [h7₁₄]\n          contradiction\n        exact ⟨x, ⟨h7₇, h7₉⟩, h7₈⟩\n      -- Show that the function is bijective\n      have h7₄ : ({x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} : Set U) ∼ ({x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} : Set V) := by\n        -- Use the fact that the function is injective and surjective\n        have h7₅ : one_to_one_on f {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} := by\n          intro x hx y hy hxy\n          have h7₆ : x ∈ A := hx.1\n          have h7₇ : x ≠ a := hx.2\n          have h7₈ : y ∈ A := hy.1\n          have h7₉ : y ≠ a := hy.2\n          have h7₁₀ : one_one_on f A := h1\n          have h7₁₁ : x ∈ A := h7₆\n          have h7₁₂ : y ∈ A := h7₈\n          have h7₁₃ : f x = f y := hxy\n          have h7₁₄ : x = y := h7₁₀ h7₁₁ h7₁₂ h7₁₃\n          exact h7₁₄\n        -- Use the fact that the function is surjective\n        have h7₆ : ∀ (y : V), y ∈ {x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} → ∃ (x : U), x ∈ {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} ∧ f x = y := h7₃\n        -- Use the fact that the function is injective and surjective to show that the sets are equinumerous\n        have h7₇ : ({x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} : Set U) ∼ ({x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} : Set V) := by\n          -- Use the fact that the function is injective and surjective to show that the sets are equinumerous\n          have h7₈ : Set.InjOn f {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} := by\n            intro x hx y hy hxy\n            exact h7₅ hx hy hxy\n          have h7₉ : Set.SurjOn (fun x : U => f x) {x : U | x ∈ A ∧ x ≠ a} {x : V | x ∈ B ∧ x ≠ b} := by\n            intro y hy\n            obtain ⟨x, hx, hxy⟩ := h7₃ y hy\n            exact ⟨x, hx, hxy⟩\n          -- Use the fact that the function is injective and surjective to show that the sets are equinumerous\n          exact Set.equinumerous_of_injective_of_surjective f h7₈ h7₉\n        exact h7₇\n      exact h7₄\n    exact h7₁\n  \n  have h8 : ↑(A \\ {a}) ∼ ↑(B \\ {b}) := by\n    rw [h5]\n    rw [h6]\n    exact h7\n  \n  exact h8",
      "by\n  have h5 : image f (A \\ ({a} : Set U)) = B \\ {b} := by\n    have h6 : image f (A \\ ({a} : Set U)) = image f A \\ {f a} := by\n      ext y\n      simp [Set.mem_image, Set.mem_diff, Set.mem_singleton_iff]\n      <;>\n      (try tauto) <;>\n      (try {\n        aesop\n      }) <;>\n      (try {\n        constructor <;>\n        (try {\n          intro h <;>\n          (try {\n            aesop\n          }) <;>\n          (try {\n            simp_all [Set.mem_image, Set.mem_diff, Set.mem_singleton_iff]\n            <;>\n            (try {\n              aesop\n            })\n          })\n        }) <;>\n        (try {\n          aesop\n        })\n      })\n      <;>\n      (try {\n        aesop\n      })\n    rw [h6]\n    have h7 : image f A = B := h2\n    rw [h7]\n    have h8 : f a = b := h4\n    rw [h8]\n    <;>\n    simp [Set.ext_iff]\n    <;>\n    tauto\n  \n  have h9 : (A \\ ({a} : Set U)) ∼ (B \\ ({b} : Set V)) := by\n    have h10 : one_one_on f (A \\ ({a} : Set U)) := by\n      intro x hx y hy hxy\n      have h11 : x ∈ A \\ ({a} : Set U) := hx\n      have h12 : y ∈ A \\ ({a} : Set U) := hy\n      have h13 : f x = f y := hxy\n      have h14 : one_one_on f A := h1\n      have h15 : x ∈ A := by\n        simp only [Set.mem_diff] at h11\n        exact h11.1\n      have h16 : y ∈ A := by\n        simp only [Set.mem_diff] at h12\n        exact h12.1\n      have h17 : x ≠ a := by\n        simp only [Set.mem_diff] at h11\n        exact h11.2\n      have h18 : y ≠ a := by\n        simp only [Set.mem_diff] at h12\n        exact h12.2\n      have h19 : x = y := by\n        apply h14\n        <;>\n        (try simp_all [Set.mem_diff]) <;>\n        (try tauto) <;>\n        (try aesop)\n        <;>\n        (try {\n          simp_all [Set.mem_diff]\n          <;>\n          tauto\n        })\n      exact h19\n    have h20 : Set.Eq (image f (A \\ ({a} : Set U))) (B \\ {b}) := by\n      ext y\n      simp_all [Set.mem_image, Set.mem_diff, Set.mem_singleton_iff]\n      <;>\n      (try tauto) <;>\n      (try {\n        aesop\n      }) <;>\n      (try {\n        constructor <;>\n        (try {\n          intro h <;>\n          (try {\n            aesop\n          }) <;>\n          (try {\n            simp_all [Set.mem_image, Set.mem_diff, Set.mem_singleton_iff]\n            <;>\n            (try {\n              aesop\n            })\n          })\n        }) <;>\n        (try {\n          aesop\n        })\n      })\n      <;>\n      (try {\n        aesop\n      })\n    -- Use the fact that the image of the restricted function is the desired set and the function is injective to establish a bijection\n    have h21 : (A \\ ({a} : Set U)) ∼ (image f (A \\ ({a} : Set U))) := by\n      apply SetEquiv.of_injective\n      · intro x\n        exact ⟨f x, Set.mem_image_of_mem _ (by\n          simp_all [Set.mem_diff]\n          <;>\n          tauto\n          )⟩\n      · intro x y h\n        simp_all [Set.mem_image]\n        <;>\n        (try aesop)\n        <;>\n        (try {\n          have h22 := h10\n          simp_all [one_one_on]\n          <;>\n          aesop\n        })\n        <;>\n        (try {\n          aesop\n        })\n    have h22 : (image f (A \\ ({a} : Set U))) ∼ (B \\ ({b} : Set V)) := by\n      apply SetEquiv.ofEq\n      <;> simp_all\n      <;>\n      (try {\n        aesop\n      })\n      <;>\n      (try {\n        simp_all [Set.ext_iff]\n        <;>\n        tauto\n      })\n    -- Combine the equivalences to get the final result\n    calc\n      (A \\ ({a} : Set U)) ∼ (image f (A \\ ({a} : Set U))) := h21\n      _ ∼ (B \\ ({b} : Set V)) := h22\n  \n  exact h9",
      "by\n  have h5 : ↑(A \\ {a}) ∼ ↑(B \\ {b}) := by\n    have h6 : (A \\ {a} : Set U) ∼ (B \\ {b} : Set V) := by\n      have h7 : (image f (A \\ {a}) : Set V) = B \\ {b} := by\n        calc\n          image f (A \\ {a}) = (image f A : Set V) \\ {f a} := by\n            ext y\n            constructor\n            · intro hy\n              simp_all [image, Set.mem_diff, Set.mem_singleton_iff, exists_prop]\n              <;> aesop\n            · intro hy\n              simp_all [image, Set.mem_diff, Set.mem_singleton_iff, exists_prop]\n              <;> aesop\n          _ = B \\ {f a} := by rw [h2]\n          _ = B \\ {b} := by\n            rw [h4]\n          <;> simp [Set.ext_iff]\n      have h8 : (A \\ {a} : Set U) ∼ (image f (A \\ {a}) : Set V) := by\n        -- Use the restriction of `f` to `A \\ {a}` to establish a bijection\n        refine' Set.ofBijective (fun x : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U) => ⟨f (x.val), _⟩) _ _\n        · -- Show that `f x.val` is in `image f (A \\ {a})`\n          have h9 : f (x.val) ∈ image f (A \\ {a}) := by\n            apply Set.mem_image_of_mem\n            exact Set.mem_of_subset (Icc_subset_Icc_right h3.compl) ⟨x.val, x.property, rfl⟩\n          exact h9\n        · -- Injectivity\n          refine' fun ⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ ⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ h => _\n          have h10 : f ( (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ) = y₁ := by\n            simp [Set.mem_Icc] at hy₁ ⊢\n            <;> aesop\n          have h11 : f ( (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ) = y₂ := by\n            simp [Set.mem_Icc] at hy₂ ⊢\n            <;> aesop\n          have h12 : (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ∈ A \\ {a} := by\n            exact (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).property\n          have h13 : (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ∈ A \\ {a} := by\n            exact (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).property\n          have h14 : (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val = (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val := by\n            have h15 : f ( (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ) = f ( (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ) := by\n              simp_all [Set.mem_Icc]\n            have h16 : (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ∈ A := by\n              simp [Set.mem_Icc] at h12 ⊢\n              <;> aesop\n            have h17 : (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ∈ A := by\n              simp [Set.mem_Icc] at h13 ⊢\n              <;> aesop\n            have h18 : f ( (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ) = f ( (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val ) := by\n              simp_all [Set.mem_Icc]\n            have h19 : (⟨y₁, hy₁⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val = (⟨y₂, hy₂⟩ : Set.Icc (A \\ {a} : Set U)).val := by\n              apply h1\n              <;> aesop\n              <;> simp_all [Set.mem_Icc]\n            exact h19\n          simp_all [Set.Icc.ext_iff]\n        · -- Surjectivity\n          refine' fun y hy => _\n          have h20 : y ∈ image f (A \\ {a}) := by\n            simp_all [Set.mem_Icc]\n          rcases h20 with ⟨x, hx, rfl⟩\n          refine' ⟨⟨x, _⟩, _⟩\n          <;> simp_all [Set.mem_Icc]\n          <;> aesop\n      have h21 : (A \\ {a} : Set U) ∼ (B \\ {b} : Set V) := by\n        calc\n          (A \\ {a} : Set U) ∼ (image f (A \\ {a}) : Set V) := h8\n          _ = (B \\ {b} : Set V) := by rw [h7]\n      exact h21\n    exact Set.equivOfBijective (Set.ofSetEquiv h6)\n  exact h5",
