`_ : f x ∈ B ∧ f x ≠ b`.\n\n### Constructing `h : B \\ {b} → A \\ {a}`\n\nGiven `⟨y, hy⟩ : B \\ {b}`, we have `y ∈ B = image f A`, so there exists some `x ∈ A` such that `f x = y`. \n\nBut since `y ≠ b = f a`, and `f` is injective on `A`, we have `x ≠ a`. \n\nThus `x ∈ A \\ {a}`, and we can set `h ⟨y, hy⟩ = ⟨x, _⟩`, where `_ :",
